en:
Let $\mathcal{H}^{
u}$ denote the irreducible representation of the special unitary group$\SU(n)$ corresponding to Young diagram $
u$ and let $\mathfrak{g} = \su(n)$ denote the Lie algebra of $\SU(n)$.One can show that $\mathcal{H}^{
u}$ appears in the symmetric algebra $\operatorname{S}^*\mathfrak{g}$ if and onlyif $n$ divides the size of the Young diagram $
u$. Kostant's problem asks what is the least number $N$ such that$\mathcal{H}^{
u}$ appear in $\operatorname{S}^N\mathfrak{g}$. The 	extit{moment polytope} of the adjointrepresentation is the polytope generated by the normalized weights $	ilde{
u}$ such that $\mathcal{H}^{
u}$appears in $\operatorname{S}^*\mathfrak{g}$ and it helps to put lower bounds on number $N$ in the Kostant's problem.In this thesis, we compute the moment polytope of the adjoint representation of $\SU(n)$ for $n \leq 9$ using the solutions of the classical spectral problem and so-called $
u$-representability problem.
